<item>
            <title>[FLINK-29153] KafkaConsumerThread should catch WakeupException when committing offsets</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-29153</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumerThread&lt;/tt&gt; in the legacy &lt;tt&gt;FlinkKafkaConsumer&lt;/tt&gt; makes a wakeup on the &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer&lt;/tt&gt; on offset commit to wakeup the potential blocking &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer.poll()&lt;/tt&gt;. However the wakeup might happen when the consumer is not polling. The wakeup will be remembered by the consumer and re-examined while committing the offset asynchronously, which leads to an unnecessary &lt;tt&gt;WakeupException&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the JavaDoc and method signature of KafkaConsumer does not show that the WakeupException could be thrown in KafkaConsumer#commitAsync, this could be considered as a bug on Kafka side (breaking the contract of public API), but we can still fix it by catching the WakeupException and retrying. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
